sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>(service-ca TLS)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306/TCP
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/9000/TCP
    participant Operator as MLflow Operator<br/>controller-runtime

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,MLflow: Flow 1: External User Access via Gateway
        Client->>Gateway: POST /mlflow/api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/list<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Platform OIDC/OAuth
        Gateway->>MLflow: Forward to /api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/list<br/>HTTPS 8443/TCP (re-encrypted, service-ca)<br/>Forwarded user identity
        MLflow->>K8sAPI: SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Impersonated user token
        K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Authorization decision<br/>(check mlflow.kubeflow.org/experiments)
        MLflow-->>Gateway: JSON Response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over MLflow,DB: Flow 2: Backend Store Access
        MLflow->>DB: SQL query (experiments, runs, models)<br/>PostgreSQL 5432/TCP or MySQL 3306/TCP<br/>TLS (optional, via combined CA bundle)<br/>Auth: Connection string credentials
        DB-->>MLflow: Query results
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over MLflow,S3: Flow 3: Artifact Storage Access
        MLflow->>S3: PUT/GET model artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP or HTTP 9000/TCP<br/>TLS (via combined CA bundle)<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials (envFrom secret)
        S3-->>MLflow: Artifact data
    end

    rect rgb(248, 240, 255)
        Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch MLflow CRs<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: MLflow CR change event
        Note over Operator: Render Helm chart in-process
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply<br/>(Deployment, Service, HTTPRoute,<br/>NetworkPolicy, RBAC, ServiceMonitor)<br/>HTTPS 6443/TCP TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Apply result
    end
